      <hedline>
        <hl1>Correction</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The $25 and Under column last Wednesday, about the Colombian restaurant Las Americas in Queens, referred incorrectly to a region of Colombia that is home to a dish called bandejas Paisa. People who live in Antioquia and other northwestern provinces are colloquially known as Paisas, and the area is known as the Paisa region, but the area is not called Paisa.</p>
      </block>
